WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.200
Do you feel that communication with AI

2
00:00:02.200 --> 00:00:05.240
seems to always be separated into something?

3
00:00:05.240 --> 00:00:07.040
Today, let's talk about

4
00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:09.640
how to master such a detailed art

5
00:00:09.640 --> 00:00:12.520
to turn AI from a tool that only listens to instructions

6
00:00:12.520 --> 00:00:15.920
to become the strongest thinking partner around you.

7
00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:17.320
Have you ever had this experience?

8
00:00:17.320 --> 00:00:20.000
It's just that you got into your mind and asked a question.

9
00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:21.560
As a result, the answer given by AI

10
00:00:21.560 --> 00:00:23.800
is completely wrong.

11
00:00:23.800 --> 00:00:25.400
You ask Dong, he answers Qi.

12
00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:28.960
The whole thing is super speechless, right?

13
00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:31.040
Don't worry, you're not alone.

14
00:00:31.040 --> 00:00:32.680
The difference in communication

15
00:00:32.680 --> 00:00:35.600
is the core problem we're going to solve today.

16
00:00:35.600 --> 00:00:36.880
What should we do?

17
00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:37.920
The key is that

18
00:00:37.920 --> 00:00:39.920
we have to build a communication bridge

19
00:00:39.920 --> 00:00:41.920
between the ideas in your head

20
00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:43.920
and the execution capabilities of AI.

21
00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:45.560
And the technology to build this bridge

22
00:00:45.560 --> 00:00:48.360
is the core ability we're going to talk about today.

23
00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:51.640
That's right, we call this core ability description.

24
00:00:51.640 --> 00:00:53.240
But wait a minute,

25
00:00:53.240 --> 00:00:57.640
this is not just as simple as writing a prompt as we usually say.

26
00:00:57.680 --> 00:01:01.240
It's actually a more comprehensive communication technique

27
00:01:01.240 --> 00:01:04.680
that allows us to accurately explain tasks to AI

28
00:01:04.680 --> 00:01:06.800
and provide him with the background information he needs.

29
00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:09.040
Then, in the entire interaction process,

30
00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:11.880
guide him to achieve the goal we want.

31
00:01:11.880 --> 00:01:14.440
Is it going to be difficult to master this art?

32
00:01:14.440 --> 00:01:15.920
In fact, to put it bluntly,

33
00:01:15.920 --> 00:01:18.120
you only need to grasp three key concepts.

34
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:19.520
Really, just these three.

35
00:01:19.520 --> 00:01:20.920
And once you understand,

36
00:01:20.920 --> 00:01:22.720
the way you interact with AI

37
00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:24.800
will be completely different.

38
00:01:24.800 --> 00:01:26.640
Okay, what are these three pillars?

39
00:01:26.640 --> 00:01:27.840
They are

40
00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:30.920
First, the product description of the product produced by force.

41
00:01:30.920 --> 00:01:33.880
Second, the process description of the guidance method.

42
00:01:33.880 --> 00:01:34.840
And third,

43
00:01:34.840 --> 00:01:35.840
this is very interesting,

44
00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:38.440
the performance description of the setting atmosphere.

45
00:01:38.440 --> 00:01:40.880
As long as you cover these three pillars tightly,

46
00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:44.440
your communication with AI will be stable.

47
00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:47.640
Okay, let's start with the first one.

48
00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:51.640
How exactly do you want to accurately describe what you want?

49
00:01:51.640 --> 00:01:54.400
This is the so-called product description.

50
00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:55.320
To put it simply,

51
00:01:55.320 --> 00:01:56.840
the ability of product description

52
00:01:56.840 --> 00:02:00.120
is that you have to be able to clearly define

53
00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:03.720
what kind of product you want AI to create in the end.

54
00:02:03.720 --> 00:02:05.040
Not just roughly,

55
00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:06.600
but very accurately.

56
00:02:06.600 --> 00:02:08.760
How big is the difference?

57
00:02:08.760 --> 00:02:10.480
Come on, let's imagine

58
00:02:10.480 --> 00:02:11.560
you tell AI,

59
00:02:11.560 --> 00:02:13.720
hey, help me prepare dinner.

60
00:02:13.720 --> 00:02:15.880
This is too vague.

61
00:02:15.880 --> 00:02:17.640
How does he know what you want to eat?

62
00:02:17.640 --> 00:02:19.480
But if you change the way you say,

63
00:02:19.480 --> 00:02:21.800
hey, I want to make Italian chicken noodles.

64
00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:23.080
Give me a recipe.

65
00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:24.720
You have to have all the ingredients

66
00:02:24.720 --> 00:02:27.240
and super detailed cooking steps on it.

67
00:02:27.240 --> 00:02:29.480
Look, is this super clear?

68
00:02:29.480 --> 00:02:32.160
This is a 100% product description.

69
00:02:32.160 --> 00:02:33.400
So the point is,

70
00:02:33.400 --> 00:02:37.440
please don't let AI guess what you want.

71
00:02:37.440 --> 00:02:39.200
You have to tell him clearly,

72
00:02:39.200 --> 00:02:41.320
hey, what is the background of this job?

73
00:02:41.320 --> 00:02:42.760
What do you want him to do?

74
00:02:42.760 --> 00:02:44.440
Make it clear step by step.

75
00:02:44.440 --> 00:02:46.360
What kind of format do you want to use in the end?

76
00:02:46.360 --> 00:02:47.920
Wordang or簡報?

77
00:02:47.920 --> 00:02:49.720
Then who wants to see this thing?

78
00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:52.200
Is it for the boss or the client?

79
00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:53.640
What kind of style do you want in the end?

80
00:02:53.640 --> 00:02:55.640
More shocking or more lively?

81
00:02:55.640 --> 00:02:57.360
These things have to be said clearly.

82
00:02:57.360 --> 00:02:59.800
Okay, it's not enough to know what you want.

83
00:02:59.800 --> 00:03:01.840
Sometimes more importantly,

84
00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:04.560
how do you guide AI to do?

85
00:03:04.560 --> 00:03:06.720
This brings us to the second pillar,

86
00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:08.240
the process description.

87
00:03:08.240 --> 00:03:09.680
The process description,

88
00:03:09.680 --> 00:03:10.640
in private,

89
00:03:10.640 --> 00:03:11.760
is to guide AI

90
00:03:11.760 --> 00:03:14.320
on how to do this thing.

91
00:03:14.320 --> 00:03:15.760
Remember, sometimes

92
00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:17.160
give AI a map,

93
00:03:17.160 --> 00:03:18.520
that is, that process,

94
00:03:18.520 --> 00:03:20.160
will be more important

95
00:03:20.160 --> 00:03:21.360
than you just tell him the end,

96
00:03:21.400 --> 00:03:22.400
more important,

97
00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:23.800
and more efficient.

98
00:03:23.800 --> 00:03:25.640
How to guide?

99
00:03:25.640 --> 00:03:27.480
There are probably several ways.

100
00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:29.440
You can give him a manual,

101
00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:31.720
which is a guide to some major directions.

102
00:03:31.720 --> 00:03:34.080
Or you can give him a recipe,

103
00:03:34.080 --> 00:03:36.200
telling him in detail

104
00:03:36.200 --> 00:03:37.320
what to do first,

105
00:03:37.320 --> 00:03:38.560
what to do second.

106
00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:42.040
You can even show it to him in person

107
00:03:42.040 --> 00:03:43.120
and use some examples

108
00:03:43.120 --> 00:03:45.280
to let him learn your method.

109
00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:46.280
Think about it.

110
00:03:46.280 --> 00:03:48.160
Although AI's knowledge library is wide,

111
00:03:48.160 --> 00:03:51.080
but he doesn't know the unique situation you have.

112
00:03:51.080 --> 00:03:52.640
So you can tell him

113
00:03:52.640 --> 00:03:54.720
I have some specific information here,

114
00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:56.520
please use these to analyze.

115
00:03:56.520 --> 00:03:58.560
Or you have to deal with these problems

116
00:03:58.560 --> 00:03:59.840
in the order after.

117
00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:01.160
Or I need you to use

118
00:04:01.160 --> 00:04:02.960
a specific analysis style,

119
00:04:02.960 --> 00:04:04.440
or we have a standard

120
00:04:04.440 --> 00:04:05.920
working process in our company,

121
00:04:05.920 --> 00:04:07.040
you have to follow it.

122
00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:07.920
Tell you what,

123
00:04:07.920 --> 00:04:10.040
take some time to talk about these details.

124
00:04:10.040 --> 00:04:11.960
The result will be much worse.

125
00:04:11.960 --> 00:04:13.840
Okay, now we come to the third,

126
00:04:13.840 --> 00:04:15.560
which is also the most

127
00:04:15.560 --> 00:04:16.120
um,

128
00:04:16.120 --> 00:04:17.040
the most delicate,

129
00:04:17.040 --> 00:04:19.400
the most interesting pillar.

130
00:04:19.400 --> 00:04:22.480
How to set the atmosphere of your interaction with AI?

131
00:04:22.480 --> 00:04:24.440
We call it performance description.

132
00:04:24.440 --> 00:04:27.200
If you can only remember one sentence in today's content,

133
00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:28.840
then I hope it's this sentence.

134
00:04:28.840 --> 00:04:30.640
AI tools are not database,

135
00:04:30.640 --> 00:04:32.320
nor automatic vending machines.

136
00:04:32.320 --> 00:04:34.080
They are interactive systems

137
00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:35.840
that have different behavior modes

138
00:04:35.840 --> 00:04:37.680
because of the different circumstances you give them.

139
00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:39.600
Really, it's very similar to people.

140
00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:43.200
This is the most important part of performance description.

141
00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:46.040
You have to define the behavior mode

142
00:04:46.040 --> 00:04:48.640
when AI interacts with you.

143
00:04:48.640 --> 00:04:49.600
In other words,

144
00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:51.880
you don't just tell him what to do,

145
00:04:51.880 --> 00:04:52.880
how to do,

146
00:04:52.880 --> 00:04:54.120
you also tell him

147
00:04:54.120 --> 00:04:57.000
what role you are going to play today.

148
00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:59.280
So next time you open AI,

149
00:04:59.280 --> 00:05:00.680
you can ask yourself

150
00:05:00.680 --> 00:05:03.840
what kind of thinking partner do I need now?

151
00:05:03.840 --> 00:05:06.960
Do I need a partner who will challenge me and refute me?

152
00:05:06.960 --> 00:05:10.080
Or do I need someone who is obedient and follows me?

153
00:05:10.080 --> 00:05:13.120
I want him to give me super detailed information

154
00:05:13.120 --> 00:05:13.720
or

155
00:05:13.720 --> 00:05:15.520
just focus on the point.

156
00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:18.360
I need him to explain the thinking process of each step

157
00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:20.440
or just give me the answer directly.

158
00:05:20.440 --> 00:05:21.240
You see,

159
00:05:21.240 --> 00:05:22.800
these choices will create

160
00:05:22.800 --> 00:05:24.800
completely different AI partners.

161
00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:27.250
Okay, we've finished reading the three pillars.

162
00:05:28.650 --> 00:05:31.770
When you combine the three descriptions

163
00:05:31.770 --> 00:05:34.130
of the product, process, and performance

164
00:05:34.130 --> 00:05:35.930
that you just mentioned,

165
00:05:35.930 --> 00:05:38.370
what magical things will happen?

166
00:05:38.370 --> 00:05:39.810
The final result is

167
00:05:39.810 --> 00:05:41.210
you turn AI from

168
00:05:41.210 --> 00:05:42.810
an assistant you know

169
00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:44.450
who is very common, like a can,

170
00:05:44.450 --> 00:05:46.130
into a person who is completely

171
00:05:46.170 --> 00:05:47.330
a person who knows you

172
00:05:47.330 --> 00:05:50.170
and can help you solve those super complicated problems.

173
00:05:50.170 --> 00:05:52.010
A super powerful tool.

174
00:05:52.010 --> 00:05:54.770
So this brings a question that is worth thinking about.

175
00:05:54.770 --> 00:05:56.210
After listening to these today,

176
00:05:56.210 --> 00:05:58.170
what kind of thinking partner

177
00:05:58.170 --> 00:06:00.170
do you want to create first?
